Apply for UI beneﬁts (called ﬁling an initial claim) in the U.S. state or district where you worked, not where you live. You may ﬁle:
● in the online BEACON UI system (beacon.labor.maryland.gov/);
● by phone at 667-207-6520 (Monday to Friday, 8:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.).

After you apply, you must meet weekly eligibility requirements to receive UI beneﬁt payments, which include:
● be able and available for work (without undue restrictions) and meet work search requirements (see question #6);
● ﬁle weekly claim certiﬁcations on time (see question #5);
o acceptsuitablework whenoffered |
● accept suitable work, when offered;
● be available and contact the Maryland Division of Unemployment Insurance and/or the Maryland Division of Workforce Development and Adult Learning (DWDAL) when instructed;
○ You may be selected for a Reemployment Services and Eligibility Assessment (RESEA) workshop.
● report payments on your weekly claim certiﬁcation (any wages, self-employment income, tips, commission, ﬁrst payment from a pension you did not previously report, etc.). Do not report Social Security income.
NOTE: If you receive certain payments (severance, vacation, holiday, bonus, back pay or damages, or other special payments) after ﬁling an initial claim, report it by calling a claims agent at (667) 207-6520.
